{
  "texts": [
    "Podcast Assessment: When considering podcast summarization with long inputs of over 5k tokens on average, only Llama2 models (which have a limit of 4k tokens) were used (as FlanT5 has a limit of 1k tokens).",
    "Table 2 shows that comparative assessment yields highly impressive performance for long-spoken summarization, with comparative assessment out-competing all other baselines.",
    "Further, although prompt-scoring has good systemlevel correlations, the lack of granularity leads to poor summary-level performance.",
    "Dialogue Assessment: Next, we analyze comparative assessment on TopicalChat, for evaluating conversational responses.",
    "Table 3 shows similar findings for TopicalChat as to those in SummEval, where comparative assessment again outperforms the correlations seen from prompt-scoring."
  ]
}